// GAP-5 (MEDIUM) — orelse-reassignment overwrites alive Handle silently
//
// Re-assigning a Handle local that is currently ALIVE (without freeing
// first) should be a leak. The pattern `h = pool.alloc() orelse return;`
// decomposes to IR_COPY into the dest. IR_COPY's overwrite-leak check
// (F3.1 partial fix 2026-05-03) did not reach this orelse-wrapped form.
// First allocation leaks.
//
// Compile-time: passes (no warning, no error).
// Runtime: first slot leaked; subsequent calls hit a different slot.

Slab(u32) heap;

i32 main() {
    Handle(u32) h = heap.alloc() orelse return;
    h = heap.alloc() orelse return;  // first allocation leaked silently
    heap.free(h);
    return 0;
}
